title: "URL Encode & Decode"
description: "Free online URL encoder and decoder. Encode special characters for URLs or decode percent-encoded strings instantly. No signup required."
layout: tool.njk
tool: true
date: 2026-04-27
---

<div class="tool-container">
  <div class="tool-header">
    <h1>URL Encode & Decode</h1>
    <p>Encode text for safe use in URLs, or decode percent-encoded strings back to readable text. All processing happens in your browser.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="tool-main">
    <div class="tool-panel">
      <div class="panel-header">
        <span>Input</span>
        <div class="panel-actions">
          <button onclick="pasteFromClipboard()" class="btn btn-sm">Paste</button>
          <button onclick="clearAll()" class="btn btn-sm">Clear</button>
        </div>
      </div>
      <textarea id="url-input" placeholder="Enter text to encode, or %XX string to decode..." spellcheck="false"></textarea>
    </div>

    <div class="tool-actions">
      <button onclick="encodeURL()" class="btn btn-primary">Encode →</button>
      <button onclick="encodeURLComponent()" class="btn btn-secondary">Encode Component →</button>
      <button onclick="decodeURL()" class="btn btn-secondary">← Decode</button>
    </div>

    <div class="tool-panel">
      <div class="panel-header">
        <span>Output</span>
        <div class="panel-actions">
          <button onclick="swapValues()" class="btn btn-sm">Swap</button>
          <button onclick="copyOutput()" class="btn btn-sm">Copy</button>
        </div>
      </div>
      <textarea id="url-output" readonly placeholder="Result will appear here..."></textarea>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div id="status-bar" class="status-bar"></div>
</div>

<div class="tool-features">
  <h2>Features</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Two encoding modes</strong> — <code>encodeURI</code> preserves URL structure (/?:@&=+#), <code>encodeURIComponent</code> encodes everything</li>
    <li><strong>UTF-8 Support</strong> — Handles Chinese, emoji, and other Unicode characters</li>
    <li><strong>Privacy</strong> — All processing is client-side</li>
  </ul>
</div>

<div class="tool-seo">
  <h2>encodeURI vs encodeURIComponent</h2>
  <p>Use <strong>encodeURI</strong> when you have a complete URL that needs encoding. It preserves URL-reserved characters like <code>/</code>, <code>?</code>, <code>&</code>, <code>=</code> so the URL structure stays intact.</p>
  <p>Use <strong>encodeURIComponent</strong> when encoding a single query parameter value. It encodes ALL special characters including <code>/</code> and <code>&</code>, preventing injection into the URL structure.</p>

  <h2>When to URL Encode</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Passing special characters in query string parameters</li>
    <li>Constructing URLs with user-provided input</li>
    <li>Encoding data for <code>application/x-www-form-urlencoded</code> requests</li>
    <li>Handling Chinese or other non-ASCII characters in URLs</li>
  </ul>
</div>

